
PREREQUISITES:
-------------
Building for Windows is only tested for the MinGW cross-compilation environment, http://mingw-cross-env.nongnu.org


BUILDING FROM SOURCE:
--------------------

1. Install cmake. You will need it for building. 

2. Build and install:

  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake ..
  make
  make install

3. Download and build SuperCollider sources: (optional, if you want sound)

3.1. Install 'jack2' if you want sound on Linux:
     (Ubuntu) sudo apt-get install jackd2
     (Arch)   sudo pacman -S jack2
     (Fedora) sudo yum install jack-audio-connection-kit

3.2. Check out SC sources from the repo:

  git clone --recursive git://supercollider.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/supercollider/supercollider

3.3. Build SC with a minimal required set of dependencies: (Replace '/prefix' with a real directory.)

  cd supercollider
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake -DFFT_GREEN=ON -DNO_LIBSNDFILE=ON -DSC_QT=OFF -DSUPERNOVA=OFF -DNO_AVAHI=ON -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/prefix/SuperCollider/ -DSC_WII=OFF -DSC_EL=OFF ..
  make
  make install/strip

3.4. Copy SC binaries to 'diggr-roguelike/sound/':

  cd .../diggr-roguelike/
  cd sound
  cp /prefix/SuperCollider/bin/scsynth .
  cp /prefix/SuperCollider/lib/libscsynth.so.1 .  
  cp -rf /prefix/SuperColliderlib/SuperCollider/plugins/ .

